wwpL2CFTunnelMIB.name: wwpL2CFTunnelMIB
wwpL2CFTunnelMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpL2CFTunnelMIB.description: This MIB module is for the Layer 2 Control Frame Tunneling in WWP Portal Products

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpL2CFTunnelOperStatus.name: wwpL2CFTunnelOperStatus
wwpL2CFTunnelOperStatus.description: The current operational state of tunnel.

wwpL2CFTunnelAdminStatus.name: wwpL2CFTunnelAdminStatus
wwpL2CFTunnelAdminStatus.description: The administratively desired status of Layer 2 control frame handling.

wwpL2CFTunnelPriority.name: wwpL2CFTunnelPriority
wwpL2CFTunnelPriority.description: The 802.1p packet priority to be assigned to packets associated with this port that do not have an 802.1Q VLAN header.

wwpL2CFTunnelRowStatus.name: wwpL2CFTunnelRowStatus
wwpL2CFTunnelRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. The default state for wwpL2CFTunnelAdminStatus will be 'disabled'.

wwpL2CFTProtocolTable.name: wwpL2CFTProtocolTable
wwpL2CFTProtocolTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the l2 control frame protocol status tunnels.

wwpL2CFTProtocolEntry.name: wwpL2CFTProtocolEntry
wwpL2CFTProtocolEntry.description: The layer 2 control frame protocol tunnel entry.

wwpL2CFTProtocolNum.name: wwpL2CFTProtocolNum
wwpL2CFTProtocolNum.description: This object represent the list of protocols the device can support.

wwpL2CFTDispositionType.name: wwpL2CFTDispositionType
wwpL2CFTDispositionType.description: Setting this object to 'discard' will cause wwpL2CFTProtocolNum frames arriving at the specified port to be discarded. NOTE: Setting this to 'peer' will cause the wwpL2CFTProtocolNum frame to be processed in the same manor as 'discard'. Setting this to 'tunnel' will cause the wwpL2CFTProtocolNum frame to be tunneled. The default disposition state of each protocol is controlled by portal application.

wwpL2CFTStatsTable.name: wwpL2CFTStatsTable
wwpL2CFTStatsTable.description: A table that contains the frame counters for Layer 2 control frame handling.

wwpL2CFTStatsEntry.name: wwpL2CFTStatsEntry
wwpL2CFTStatsEntry.description: A list of Link Aggregation Control Protocol statistics for each port on this device.

wwpL2CFTStatsProtocolNum.name: wwpL2CFTStatsProtocolNum
wwpL2CFTStatsProtocolNum.description: This object represent the list of protocols the device can support.

wwpL2CFTStatsPacketsRx.name: wwpL2CFTStatsPacketsRx
wwpL2CFTStatsPacketsRx.description: The number of number of pkts ingressed matching protocol. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsTunneledFrames.name: wwpL2CFTStatsTunneledFrames
wwpL2CFTStatsTunneledFrames.description: The number of number of pts that made tunneled. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFrames.name: wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFrames
wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFrames.description: The number of came in tunneled, then restored. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFailed.name: wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFailed
wwpL2CFTStatsDecodedFailed.description: The number of failed to untunnel. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsPeeredFrames.name: wwpL2CFTStatsPeeredFrames
wwpL2CFTStatsPeeredFrames.description: The number of number of peered packets. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsDiscardFrames.name: wwpL2CFTStatsDiscardFrames
wwpL2CFTStatsDiscardFrames.description: The number of number of discarded packets. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTStatsTunFrameSubPort.name: wwpL2CFTStatsTunFrameSubPort
wwpL2CFTStatsTunFrameSubPort.description: The number of number of tunneled frames received on subscriber port. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPacketsRx.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPacketsRx
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPacketsRx.description: The total number of number of frames ingressed matching protocol. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunneledFrames.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunneledFrames
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunneledFrames.description: The total number of number of frames that made tunneled. This total value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFrames.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFrames
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFrames.description: The total number of frames that came in tunneled, then restored. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFailed.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFailed
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDecodedFailed.description: Specifies the total number of frames that failed to 'untunnel' on the vlan. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPeeredFrames.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPeeredFrames
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsPeeredFrames.description: The total number of number of peered frames. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDiscardFrames.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDiscardFrames
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsDiscardFrames.description: The total number of number of discarded frames. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunFrameSubPort.name: wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunFrameSubPort
wwpL2CFTGlobalStatsTunFrameSubPort.description: The total number of number of tunneled frames received on subscriber port. This value is read-only.

wwpL2CFTResetStatCounters.name: wwpL2CFTResetStatCounters
wwpL2CFTResetStatCounters.description: To reset L2 control frame statistic counters , this object should be set to 'reset'. A read on this object should return none(0).
